body:

I can continue, Im not tired, but Im a little concerned..

body:

At this time of year, there are a lot of blog posts about getting fit, losing weight, joining a gym, etc. Especially after several solid weeks of overindulgence over the holidays, and the prospect of starting clean with the New Year, many of us formulate grandiose resolutions about reclaiming the bodies of our youth–even if we never had the ‘best’ body before. summary: Stressed? This Is How It Physically Damages Your Body And Causes Back Pain
title: Stressed? This Is How It Physically Damages Your Body And Causes Back Pain
excerpt: Stress is highly connected to your physical body and when it rises, your adrenal glands start to release hormones such as adrenaline, cortisol, epinephrine or norepinephrine.
description:
Stress can really make your life more difficult and it can even lead to a series of diseases. Many people can’t fight the strength to cope with stress and they end up feeling unmotivated, nervous and exhausted.

It is essential to find the reason that is causing the stress in order to beat the symptoms. Stress is connected to your mental and physical stress, so you need to learn how to control it and cope with it.

Stress usually comes from family or relationship issues, work problems and serious challenges that can build pressure. Also, chronic stress can be developed through physiological problems such as insomnia, bad thoughts, infections, and blood pressure issues.
